WEBVTT

1
00:00:28.562 --> 00:00:32.623
<i>presented by Chungeorahm Film.</i>
<i>Showbox / Mediaplex. Inc.</i>

2
00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:51.507
<i>a Chungeorahm Film production</i>

3
00:00:58.124 --> 00:01:02.493
<i>February 9. 2000</i>
<i>Morgue. U.S. Army Base - Yongsan. Korea</i>

4
00:01:05.265 --> 00:01:06.823
Mr. Kim.

5
00:01:11.471 --> 00:01:14.440
I hate dust more than anything.

6
00:01:18.478 --> 00:01:20.946
I'll... I'll clean again.

7
00:01:21.481 --> 00:01:23.745
You don't have to clean up now.

8
00:01:24.017 --> 00:01:26.281
Why don't you dump this first?

9
00:01:30.056 --> 00:01:31.614
That's formalin.

10
00:01:32.359 --> 00:01:35.419
Formaldehyde. to be precise.

11
00:01:35.562 --> 00:01:40.329
To be even more precise. dirty formaldehyde.

12
00:01:41.468 --> 00:01:45.234
Every bottle is coated with layers of dust.

13
00:01:47.173 --> 00:01:49.038
Pour them into the sink.

14
00:01:50.176 --> 00:01:51.734
Excuse me?

15
00:01:51.878 --> 00:01:55.439
Just empty every bottle to the very last drop.

16
00:01:55.582 --> 00:01:58.210
It's just... they are toxic chemicals

17
00:01:58.318 --> 00:02:00.047
and the regulation states that...

18
00:02:00.153 --> 00:02:03.213
Pour them right down the drain. Mr. Kim.

19
00:02:08.762 --> 00:02:11.253
If I pour them in the drain.

20
00:02:11.598 --> 00:02:14.066
they'll run into the Han River.

21
00:02:14.167 --> 00:02:15.293
That's right.

22
00:02:15.402 --> 00:02:17.870
Let's just dump them in the Han River.

23
00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:18.903
But. you know.

24
00:02:18.972 --> 00:02:21.839
this is not just any toxic chemical...

25
00:02:21.975 --> 00:02:25.843
The Han River is very broad. Mr. Kim.

26
00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:30.712
Let's try to be broad-minded about this.

27
00:02:33.053 --> 00:02:34.418
Anyway.

28
00:02:35.855 --> 00:02:37.322
that's an order.

29
00:02:37.524 --> 00:02:40.687
So. start pouring.

30
00:03:27.407 --> 00:03:31.639
<i>June 2002. Han River</i>

31
00:03:56.970 --> 00:03:58.938
What the heck is this?

32
00:03:59.072 --> 00:04:00.232
What?

33
00:04:02.876 --> 00:04:05.140
That's pretty gross.

34
00:04:05.678 --> 00:04:09.637
Is it a mutation?

35
00:04:10.950 --> 00:04:11.917
Is it dead?

36
00:04:12.052 --> 00:04:14.418
No. it moved a second ago.

37
00:04:14.554 --> 00:04:16.021
Yeah? Wait...

38
00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:22.721
My cup!

39
00:04:23.663 --> 00:04:25.221
That was close.

40
00:04:25.365 --> 00:04:27.026
My daughter gave me this cup.

41
00:04:27.167 --> 00:04:29.226
Look. it's swimming away.

42
00:04:30.970 --> 00:04:34.531
How many tails does that thing have?

43
00:04:34.674 --> 00:04:37.643
You got me.
Makes your skin crawl.

44
00:04:39.779 --> 00:04:42.247
- Mr. Yoon!
- Sir!
<i>October 2006. Han River Bridge</i>

45
00:04:42.382 --> 00:04:44.316
What the hell are you doing?

46
00:04:45.351 --> 00:04:46.909
Don't do it!

47
00:04:47.053 --> 00:04:48.520
No! No!

48
00:04:52.559 --> 00:04:54.117
Did you guys see that?

49
00:04:59.165 --> 00:05:00.723
Underneath...

50
00:05:02.469 --> 00:05:03.936
In the water!

51
00:05:11.377 --> 00:05:15.541
Something dark
in the water...

52
00:05:16.683 --> 00:05:18.207
You really didn't see it?

53
00:05:22.355 --> 00:05:24.414
What the hell are you talking about?

54
00:05:25.959 --> 00:05:28.427
Morons. to the very end.

55
00:05:31.064 --> 00:05:32.725
Have a good life.

56
00:05:44.577 --> 00:05:54.009
<i>THE HOST</i>

57
00:05:58.558 --> 00:06:02.824
<i>executive producers</i>
<i>CHOI Yong-bae KIM Woo-taek</i>

58
00:06:04.764 --> 00:06:07.324
<i>producer CHOI Yong-bae</i>

59
00:06:10.470 --> 00:06:14.634
<i>screenplay BONG Joon-ho.</i>
<i>HAH Joon-won. BAEKChul-hyun</i>

60
00:06:16.242 --> 00:06:19.609
<i>cinematography KIM Hyung-koo</i>

61
00:06:23.650 --> 00:06:26.118
Welcome. what would you like?

62
00:06:28.154 --> 00:06:30.019
- How much is this?
- 75 cents.

63
00:06:32.458 --> 00:06:35.427
Ah... Not again...
Lift your head.

64
00:06:40.967 --> 00:06:43.834
One. two. three...
Here you are.

65
00:06:49.976 --> 00:06:54.242
<i>make-up / hair SONG Jong-hee</i>
<i>costume CHO Sang-kyoung</i>

66
00:06:54.881 --> 00:06:56.143
Daddy!

67
00:06:56.950 --> 00:06:59.009
Hyun-seo? Hyun-seo...

68
00:06:59.152 --> 00:07:00.813
Wait for me!

69
00:07:03.456 --> 00:07:08.325
Now that you're awake...

70
00:07:08.561 --> 00:07:11.724
Three squids for mat #4.
roast them quickly.

71
00:07:12.465 --> 00:07:16.424
Gosh. how much sleep
can a body take?

72
00:07:18.271 --> 00:07:21.934
<i>director BONG Joon-ho</i>

73
00:07:43.663 --> 00:07:45.130
Hyun-seo!

74
00:07:49.869 --> 00:07:51.029
Hyun-seo!

75
00:07:51.971 --> 00:07:53.438
Here you are.

76
00:07:59.679 --> 00:08:01.340
Oh. that hurts.

77
00:08:02.982 --> 00:08:04.415
Did your uncle do a good job?

78
00:08:04.550 --> 00:08:05.812
He came. at least.

79
00:08:05.952 --> 00:08:08.318
I was worried.

80
00:08:08.454 --> 00:08:14.518
I was the only one whose
uncle came to parents' day.

81
00:08:14.661 --> 00:08:16.822
That's why I kept calling.
but you didn't answer.

82
00:08:16.963 --> 00:08:18.624
Why didn't you answer?

83
00:08:18.765 --> 00:08:21.029
You think this phone
can receive signals?

84
00:08:21.167 --> 00:08:24.330
I'm too embarrassed
to use it in public. You take it.

85
00:08:24.470 --> 00:08:25.732
What's wrong with it?

86
00:08:25.872 --> 00:08:27.737
Oh. and about uncle...

87
00:08:27.874 --> 00:08:32.038
I could smell alcohol on him
when he stood in the back of class.

88
00:08:32.178 --> 00:08:35.147
That punk.
getting drunk at this hour.

89
00:08:35.281 --> 00:08:36.805
Hasn't it started. Grandpa?

90
00:08:36.949 --> 00:08:37.711
What?

91
00:08:37.850 --> 00:08:40.216
Today's Nam-joo's competition.
aren't we gonna watch?

92
00:08:40.353 --> 00:08:42.821
Oh. Nam-joo! Right...

93
00:08:58.471 --> 00:08:59.631
Why isn't it on?

94
00:09:01.474 --> 00:09:03.533
- You know what this is?
- What?

95
00:09:03.676 --> 00:09:06.440
I'm saving up
to get you a new phone.

96
00:09:07.480 --> 00:09:08.845
There's a lot. huh?

97
00:09:12.051 --> 00:09:15.111
They're all dimes!
That'll never be enough.

98
00:09:15.655 --> 00:09:18.624
There are some quarters. too...

99
00:09:18.758 --> 00:09:21.318
What's this penny doing here?

100
00:09:21.461 --> 00:09:25.022
This is all from the change box. huh?
I'll tell Grandpa.

101
00:09:25.164 --> 00:09:28.429
- Go ahead. tell the geezer.
- Geezer?

102
00:09:28.568 --> 00:09:30.035
It's a dead body.

103
00:09:30.770 --> 00:09:32.472
<i>Today morning. Han river in Seoul</i>
That's gross.

104
00:09:32.472 --> 00:09:33.873
<i>Today morning.Han river in Seoul</i>
Why aren't they
showing the game anyway?

105
00:09:33.873 --> 00:09:36.137
<i>Today morning.Han river in Seoul</i>
Turn to 505. The sports channel.

106
00:09:37.477 --> 00:09:38.944
Oh. there it is!

107
00:09:39.078 --> 00:09:40.443
I made that for her.
Aunt!

108
00:09:40.580 --> 00:09:42.844
A bullseye every time!

109
00:09:42.982 --> 00:09:44.916
- Park Nam-joo!
- Grandpa!

110
00:09:45.051 --> 00:09:46.712
The old man has to run the shop.
let's watch it ourselves.

111
00:09:46.853 --> 00:09:49.913
What do you mean?
We all need to support her.

112
00:09:50.056 --> 00:09:51.318
Grandpa!

113
00:09:51.457 --> 00:09:54.017
Let the geezer roast some squid.

114
00:09:55.261 --> 00:09:56.523
A straw...

115
00:09:58.564 --> 00:10:01.431
Let's have a cold one.
Here.

116
00:10:01.567 --> 00:10:03.034
This is alcohol!

117
00:10:03.569 --> 00:10:05.434
You're in middle school now.

118
00:10:05.571 --> 00:10:08.039
- What? Are you really my father?
- When your daddy was in middle...

119
00:10:08.174 --> 00:10:10.938
Alright! The semi-finals!

120
00:10:11.077 --> 00:10:13.136
Wow. She looks tough.

121
00:10:16.382 --> 00:10:17.508
It's bitter!

122
00:10:18.151 --> 00:10:19.812
Go. Park Nam-joo!

123
00:10:20.253 --> 00:10:23.222
Who else could take so long to take a shot?
<i>Park Nam-joo. Kyungki. Suowon city hall</i>

124
00:10:23.356 --> 00:10:26.018
- Oh. it started.
- Nam-joo is on. You gonna watch?

125
00:10:26.159 --> 00:10:27.626
Gold medal time!

126
00:10:27.760 --> 00:10:30.729
I can't watch my daughter's matches.
I get too nervous.

127
00:10:30.863 --> 00:10:31.830
Gold medal this time!

128
00:10:31.964 --> 00:10:32.931
Gang-du.

129
00:10:33.065 --> 00:10:34.123
- Yeah?
- Come outside.

130
00:10:34.267 --> 00:10:37.532
- I have to watch this.
- Come on out.

131
00:10:39.172 --> 00:10:40.230
Now!

132
00:10:42.074 --> 00:10:47.034
I received a complaint from mat #4.

133
00:10:47.180 --> 00:10:49.842
Their squid had only nine legs.

134
00:10:49.982 --> 00:10:52.314
Did you eat one?

135
00:10:52.452 --> 00:10:53.612
No...

136
00:10:53.753 --> 00:10:59.419
Don't deny it!
Why touch other people's things?

137
00:10:59.559 --> 00:11:03.120
Think of it from the customer's
perspective. A squid...

138
00:11:03.262 --> 00:11:05.628
The torso tastes delicious.
but the legs.

139
00:11:05.765 --> 00:11:09.132
especially the longest one.
has got something special. right?

140
00:11:09.268 --> 00:11:11.828
From a paying customer's
perspective. it's important.

141
00:11:11.971 --> 00:11:16.032
Take this to mat #4.
Tell them it's on the house.

142
00:11:20.613 --> 00:11:24.014
...4. 5. 6. 7. 8. 9. 10...

143
00:11:24.150 --> 00:11:25.811
Mat #4.

144
00:11:26.552 --> 00:11:29.521
- I've brought your order.
- Oh. put it down there.

145
00:11:30.957 --> 00:11:32.822
What are you looking at?

146
00:11:32.959 --> 00:11:34.824
There's something there.
Come on.

147
00:11:38.064 --> 00:11:40.430
- There. under the bridge.
- See it?

148
00:11:41.868 --> 00:11:44.735
- Do you see it?
- How long has it been there?

149
00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:47.135
- It's been a while.
- I told you.

150
00:11:47.273 --> 00:11:49.036
Ah. it's construction equipment.

151
00:11:49.175 --> 00:11:50.733
- Something they hung...?
- No.

152
00:11:50.877 --> 00:11:53.641
Don't think so.
It's moving.

153
00:11:54.080 --> 00:11:56.048
Yeah. it just moved.
Did it?

154
00:11:59.752 --> 00:12:01.310
Bullseye!

155
00:12:01.454 --> 00:12:03.319
She's amazing!

156
00:12:03.456 --> 00:12:06.619
I'm not just saying that
because she's my daughter.

157
00:12:06.759 --> 00:12:08.920
How could she hit
the exact center like that?

158
00:12:09.061 --> 00:12:10.528
Right!

159
00:12:10.663 --> 00:12:12.221
I can't believe it!

160
00:12:12.365 --> 00:12:14.629
Let's close the stand today.

161
00:12:20.273 --> 00:12:22.639
It's going in.

162
00:12:46.599 --> 00:12:47.725
It's huge

163
00:12:48.768 --> 00:12:49.962
God. it's huge

164
00:13:01.781 --> 00:13:03.043
Did you see that?
He ate the can!

165
00:13:03.182 --> 00:13:05.412
- Maybe. it's dolphine.
- All in one gulp.

166
00:13:06.152 --> 00:13:08.017
Have some beer nuts too!

167
00:13:18.965 --> 00:13:20.523
It swam off.

168
00:13:21.467 --> 00:13:23.128
It's gone now.

169
00:13:24.770 --> 00:13:26.635
It's an amazonian river dolphin
for sure.

170
00:13:31.877 --> 00:13:35.142
This time there are ten legs.
Mister.

171
00:13:35.281 --> 00:13:37.806
This time there are ten legs.
Count them yourself.

172
00:14:17.356 --> 00:14:20.223
Run away! Everyone run away!

173
00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:49.521
<i>In Kyung-boo high way has</i>
<i>little bit of traffic jam.</i>

174
00:14:49.655 --> 00:14:52.920
<i>the traffic is going slow</i>
<i>from Soowon to Dongjak bridge.</i>

175
00:14:53.059 --> 00:14:54.117
<i>The way of Pusan...</i>

176
00:15:03.469 --> 00:15:04.436
Open up!

177
00:15:15.481 --> 00:15:18.609
Young-ho!

178
00:15:20.252 --> 00:15:23.517
My son must be in there.

179
00:15:25.057 --> 00:15:26.922
Someone help. please!

180
00:15:28.761 --> 00:15:29.625
There are people in there.
I gotta go help.

181
00:15:29.762 --> 00:15:32.128
Hey. mister. my kid...

182
00:15:32.264 --> 00:15:36.633
Donald. don't go.
Come on. Donald. Come back!

183
00:15:36.769 --> 00:15:38.031
You're gonna get hurt. Donald!

184
00:15:41.373 --> 00:15:42.237
Hey. hey. hey!

185
00:15:42.374 --> 00:15:43.739
Let me help! Let me help!

186
00:15:43.876 --> 00:15:47.243
Hey. man! Hey. man!
You're not gonna get this door open.

187
00:16:04.263 --> 00:16:05.525
Hey!

188
00:16:18.077 --> 00:16:19.635
Donald! Where're you going?

189
00:16:19.779 --> 00:16:22.942
Donald! Come Back!

190
00:16:24.450 --> 00:16:26.509
Faster! Let's go!

191
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:28.415
Throw it hard!

192
00:16:29.955 --> 00:16:31.217
Donald!

193
00:17:08.561 --> 00:17:09.528
- <i>Semi-finals...</i>
- Shoot!

194
00:17:09.662 --> 00:17:10.822
<i>This is the last shot of the semi-finals.</i>

195
00:17:10.963 --> 00:17:13.932
<i>Ooh. now is not the time to</i>
<i>lower her bow.</i>

196
00:17:14.066 --> 00:17:15.226
Shoot!

197
00:17:16.068 --> 00:17:18.935
<i>Because if she goes over the clock...</i>

198
00:17:19.071 --> 00:17:19.935
Shoot!

199
00:17:20.072 --> 00:17:21.835
<i>2. 1...</i>

200
00:17:21.974 --> 00:17:24.841
<i>Oh no! The clock!</i>

201
00:17:24.977 --> 00:17:27.036
You could have just let go.

202
00:17:27.179 --> 00:17:28.339
<i>Park's Achilles'heel</i>
<i>is taking too long to release.</i>

203
00:17:28.480 --> 00:17:30.004
<i>And today it cost her the title.</i>

204
00:17:30.149 --> 00:17:32.913
<i>She shouldn't have done that.</i>
<i>She wasted much time.</i>

205
00:17:33.052 --> 00:17:37.614
<i>Yoon Ock-hee. Kyungbook Yecheon county office</i>
<i>advanced to the final of individual woman</i>
<i>At this point. Park can only hope</i>

206
00:17:37.756 --> 00:17:39.451
<i>for the bronze.</i>

207
00:19:39.678 --> 00:19:40.736
Hyun-seo!

208
00:19:54.460 --> 00:19:57.429
- Hyun-seo!
- Hey. come back!

209
00:19:58.263 --> 00:19:59.628
Gang-du!

210
00:20:01.667 --> 00:20:04.033
- Hyun-seo!
- Hold anything!

211
00:20:04.169 --> 00:20:05.329
Hyun-seo!

212
00:20:11.877 --> 00:20:13.037
Hyun-seo!

213
00:20:17.249 --> 00:20:19.717
Hyun-seo!

214
00:20:20.853 --> 00:20:22.013
Hyun-seo!

215
00:20:27.659 --> 00:20:28.819
Sir!

216
00:20:29.862 --> 00:20:31.329
Sir!

217
00:20:33.565 --> 00:20:35.430
You have ten minutes to clear the area!

218
00:20:35.567 --> 00:20:37.034
Please take care of your things
and evacuate.

219
00:21:07.399 --> 00:21:10.334
<i>Restricted Area</i>

220
00:21:23.949 --> 00:21:25.507
Come on.

221
00:21:29.054 --> 00:21:33.491
<i>Soowon city hall</i>

222
00:22:03.956 --> 00:22:05.514
Nam-joo.

223
00:22:11.964 --> 00:22:13.329
Hyun-seo!

224
00:22:14.867 --> 00:22:17.631
It's bronze. Bronze.

225
00:22:18.370 --> 00:22:22.431
Your aunt
brought you a bronze medal.

226
00:22:32.351 --> 00:22:36.014
Hyun-seo. it's your aunt...

227
00:22:41.960 --> 00:22:43.621
Hyun-seo...

228
00:22:58.310 --> 00:23:00.039
Hyun-seo...

229
00:23:07.052 --> 00:23:10.920
Hyun-seo. your uncle came.

230
00:23:13.158 --> 00:23:20.121
Thanks to you. we're all together...

231
00:23:20.265 --> 00:23:22.233
Hyun-seo!

232
00:23:22.768 --> 00:23:26.033
Let go of me!

233
00:23:38.250 --> 00:23:40.013
What are you taking pictures of?

234
00:23:40.152 --> 00:23:42.814
What's so goddamn interesting?
Fuck off!

235
00:23:42.955 --> 00:23:44.616
Stop taking pictures!

236
00:23:45.557 --> 00:23:52.725
Calling the owner of a Hyundai car.
plate # 2487!

237
00:23:54.066 --> 00:23:59.129
Hey lady. how could
you park your car there?

238
00:24:00.872 --> 00:24:02.533
So you screwed up?

239
00:24:03.175 --> 00:24:04.836
I heard everything.

240
00:24:04.977 --> 00:24:07.138
You grabbed some other girl's hand?

241
00:24:07.279 --> 00:24:09.338
You left Hyun-seo on the ground?

242
00:24:09.481 --> 00:24:10.709
Your own daughter!

243
00:24:10.849 --> 00:24:12.908
You call yourself a fucking father?

244
00:24:13.051 --> 00:24:16.612
You son of a bitch!

245
00:24:16.755 --> 00:24:19.622
I thought it was Hyun-seo's hand...

246
00:24:30.269 --> 00:24:32.635
She's so pretty in that photo.

247
00:24:35.073 --> 00:24:40.340
She looks just like her mom
in that photo.

248
00:24:41.380 --> 00:24:45.817
Do you think her mom
even knows that she died?

249
00:24:45.951 --> 00:24:47.111
Not a chance.

250
00:24:47.753 --> 00:24:52.315
It's been 13 years since she
popped out the baby and ran off.

251
00:24:53.458 --> 00:24:55.619
I'd run away too. dammit.

252
00:24:58.363 --> 00:25:00.923
Are you sleeping? Huh?

253
00:25:01.066 --> 00:25:02.124
Nam-il...

254
00:25:02.267 --> 00:25:03.928
You can sleep at a time like this?

255
00:25:04.069 --> 00:25:05.536
What are you doing to your brother?

256
00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:19.117
Her birth was an accident...

257
00:25:20.152 --> 00:25:22.120
and so was her death...

258
00:25:25.157 --> 00:25:27.216
Old people have always said.

259
00:25:27.359 --> 00:25:33.628
that an animal which kills a human
should be torn limb from limb.

260
00:25:33.765 --> 00:25:36.427
That it's a human's duty to do so.

261
00:25:41.273 --> 00:25:47.143
Until I slit that beast's stomach and
at least find Hyun-seo's body.

262
00:25:47.279 --> 00:25:49.543
I'll never
leave this world in peace.

263
00:25:57.556 --> 00:25:58.921
Attention please!

264
00:25:59.958 --> 00:26:05.328
Ladies and gentlemen. those of you
present at the river incident...

265
00:26:05.464 --> 00:26:07.022
there are probably a lot of you here...

266
00:26:07.165 --> 00:26:12.626
This is an important matter of
life and death.

267
00:26:12.771 --> 00:26:15.137
Those who were at the scene...

268
00:26:15.273 --> 00:26:17.741
or those who have come
in contact with these people!

269
00:26:17.876 --> 00:26:19.741
Raise your hands!

270
00:26:20.779 --> 00:26:23.714
This isn't something
you should hide.

271
00:26:23.849 --> 00:26:25.510
Raise your hands.

272
00:26:27.452 --> 00:26:31.513
If you go home. it might affect
your families. Raise 'em high!

273
00:26:36.161 --> 00:26:37.321
Hey. mister.

274
00:26:37.863 --> 00:26:39.922
What the hell is going on here?

275
00:26:40.065 --> 00:26:43.330
Fuck. shouldn't you start by
explaining what's happening?

276
00:26:43.468 --> 00:26:45.129
- Yeah
- Explain!

277
00:26:45.270 --> 00:26:51.038
An explanation should
be appearing on the TV news now.

278
00:26:52.377 --> 00:26:56.245
To save time. we'll let the news
serve as explanation.

279
00:26:56.381 --> 00:26:59.908
Okay. the news... the news...

280
00:27:00.051 --> 00:27:02.212
- Take off that shit and speak!
- ...isn't on now.

281
00:27:03.155 --> 00:27:04.315
Shit...

282
00:27:04.456 --> 00:27:09.018
Anyway. from this moment.

283
00:27:09.161 --> 00:27:12.722
you fall under our control.
so start moving!

284
00:27:12.864 --> 00:27:14.422
This is for your own safety.

285
00:27:14.566 --> 00:27:19.629
We have transport buses
waiting outside now.

286
00:27:19.771 --> 00:27:23.832
Okay. please move toward
the buses in an orderly fashion.

287
00:27:23.975 --> 00:27:28.639
That's right. Watch your children.

288
00:27:30.248 --> 00:27:35.618
Oh. did anyone here touch or come
into direct contact with the creature?

289
00:27:35.754 --> 00:27:38.518
Um... I didn't touch it.

290
00:27:38.657 --> 00:27:42.525
But some of its blood
got sprayed in my face.

291
00:27:42.661 --> 00:27:44.925
Don't move! Tell him to freeze!

292
00:27:45.464 --> 00:27:47.523
Grab him! Grab that one!

293
00:27:47.666 --> 00:27:50.328
Please remain calm. people.

294
00:27:50.469 --> 00:27:53.632
What are you doing? My son
didn't touch anything!

295
00:27:53.772 --> 00:27:55.239
Let go!

296
00:27:55.373 --> 00:27:56.237
Why are you doing this?

297
00:27:56.374 --> 00:27:58.842
- Gang-du! Get out of there!
- Dad!

298
00:27:58.977 --> 00:28:00.638
- Don't go!
- Dad!

299
00:28:00.779 --> 00:28:04.010
Gang-du. don't worry.
I'm coming with you.

300
00:28:04.149 --> 00:28:06.617
Stop that!
Hey. number 31! Stop!

301
00:28:06.751 --> 00:28:07.718
<i>This is a news flash.</i>

302
00:28:07.853 --> 00:28:12.017
<i>It now appears that the creature.</i>
<i>which disappeared after its attack.</i>

303
00:28:12.157 --> 00:28:18.027
<i>on surprised parkgoers today. is far more</i>
<i>dangerous than previously assumed.</i>

304
00:28:18.163 --> 00:28:23.032
<i>U.S. Army Sgt. Donald White.</i>
<i>who fought bravely with the creature.</i>

305
00:28:23.168 --> 00:28:26.035
<i>and lost an arm in the process.</i>

306
00:28:26.171 --> 00:28:29.629
<i>is now undergoing treatment</i>
<i>at a U.S. Army hospital.</i>

307
00:28:29.774 --> 00:28:33.335
<i>After a thorough examination.</i>
<i>U.S. Army medical staff have identified.</i>

308
00:28:33.478 --> 00:28:36.140
<i>an unknown virus.</i>
<i>primarily in body parts.</i>

309
00:28:36.281 --> 00:28:39.409
<i>that came into contact</i>
<i>with the creature.</i>

310
00:28:39.551 --> 00:28:45.319
<i>I can't give any of that inform ation</i>
<i>without the approval of the United States.</i>

311
00:28:45.457 --> 00:28:48.119
<i>The U.S. Army has shipped a sample</i>
<i>of the virus to the U.S.</i>

312
00:28:48.260 --> 00:28:50.728
<i>Center for Disease Control.</i>

313
00:28:50.862 --> 00:28:54.628
which confirmed that
the creature from the Han River.

314
00:28:54.766 --> 00:28:58.634
<i>as with the Chinese civet wild cat</i>
<i>and SARS.</i>

315
00:28:58.770 --> 00:29:02.729
<i>is THE HOSTof this deadly new virus.</i>

316
00:29:02.874 --> 00:29:08.540
<i>All military units sent to pursue</i>
<i>and capture the creature.</i>

317
00:29:08.680 --> 00:29:12.309
<i>have been recalled</i>
<i>due to the risk of infection.</i>

318
00:29:12.450 --> 00:29:16.113
<i>Only special forces</i>
<i>trained in biological warfare.</i>

319
00:29:16.254 --> 00:29:21.214
<i>and disinfectant units are</i>
<i>allowed access to the Han River area.</i>

320
00:29:22.360 --> 00:29:27.229
Damn.
they made a fuss dragging us in here!

321
00:29:27.966 --> 00:29:29.331
What is this shit?

322
00:29:30.168 --> 00:29:31.726
Where are all the guys in yellow?

323
00:29:31.870 --> 00:29:33.132
Look!

324
00:29:33.672 --> 00:29:35.537
The doctors aren't
even wearing masks.

325
00:29:36.675 --> 00:29:38.233
Hello. sir!

326
00:29:38.376 --> 00:29:41.834
When might we
be allowed to go home?

327
00:29:41.980 --> 00:29:45.108
- You can't go home.
- What? We can't?

328
00:29:45.250 --> 00:29:46.615
Dad. am I dying?

329
00:29:46.751 --> 00:29:48.719
Don't say that!

330
00:29:48.853 --> 00:29:51.822
Just do what the doctors tell you.

331
00:29:51.957 --> 00:29:55.017
But Dad. my back feels itchy and weird.
Like something's moving.

332
00:29:55.160 --> 00:29:56.422
Ah. shit...

333
00:29:56.561 --> 00:29:59.325
It's a squirmy feeling.
like something's there.

334
00:29:59.464 --> 00:30:02.729
It's because
you never take a bath. it's okay.

335
00:30:02.867 --> 00:30:08.032
Attention! Numbers 25-40.
raise your hands. Quickly!

336
00:30:08.173 --> 00:30:13.338
This group. move to room 904 now.

337
00:30:13.478 --> 00:30:14.638
Not again!

338
00:30:14.779 --> 00:30:19.113
Don't tell anyone
about the blood on your face. okay?

339
00:30:19.250 --> 00:30:21.616
- Mr. Park Gang-du?
- Yes?

340
00:30:22.654 --> 00:30:26.215
You need to take a lot of tests.
so don't eat until tomorrow morning.

341
00:30:26.358 --> 00:30:27.518
What? Don't eat anything?

342
00:30:27.659 --> 00:30:29.718
Don't feed him anything!
No food!

343
00:31:24.249 --> 00:31:25.409
Hello?

344
00:31:25.950 --> 00:31:27.417
Hello?

345
00:31:28.753 --> 00:31:36.125
<i>My battery is... Hello?</i>

346
00:31:36.261 --> 00:31:37.626
<i>It's me. Hyun-seo!</i>

347
00:31:37.762 --> 00:31:41.129
<i>Dad. can you hear me?</i>
<i>Please answer me!</i>

348
00:31:41.266 --> 00:31:42.324
Is this Hyun-seo?

349
00:31:42.467 --> 00:31:46.130
<i>Dad. listen to me!</i>
<i>I can't get out!</i>

350
00:31:46.271 --> 00:31:48.239
You're alive? Where...?

351
00:31:48.373 --> 00:31:51.137
<i>It's like a big sewer.</i>
<i>Really big and deep.</i>

352
00:31:51.276 --> 00:31:53.335
Where?
Hello?

353
00:31:55.180 --> 00:31:55.874
Hyun-seo...

354
00:31:57.549 --> 00:31:58.413
- <i>Come quick!</i>
- Hyun-seo

355
00:31:58.550 --> 00:31:59.710
Is it Hyun-seo?

356
00:32:18.870 --> 00:32:20.030
What is it?

357
00:32:20.171 --> 00:32:22.833
Did you see that?

358
00:32:22.974 --> 00:32:24.532
- What?
- Wait a minute.

359
00:32:36.554 --> 00:32:38.818
Sweet!

360
00:32:38.957 --> 00:32:40.117
Hey!

361
00:32:41.459 --> 00:32:43.620
Hey. don't go near the water.

362
00:32:45.864 --> 00:32:47.126
Be careful!

363
00:32:54.372 --> 00:32:57.136
Let's go.
I'm starving.

364
00:32:57.275 --> 00:32:59.140
It's okay. get back in.

365
00:34:16.354 --> 00:34:18.914
Mister! Mister!

366
00:34:22.460 --> 00:34:23.927
Try to turn...

367
00:35:13.177 --> 00:35:16.806
Your daughter. Park Hyun-seo.
a seventh grader at Dangsan Middle School.

368
00:35:18.349 --> 00:35:20.715
