369
00:35:20.852 --> 00:35:25.016
Yes. she goes to Dangsan School...

370
00:35:25.156 --> 00:35:29.593
she's deceased.
but she's not dead.

371
00:35:33.264 --> 00:35:36.131
I mean. she died. but she's still alive.

372
00:35:36.267 --> 00:35:39.634
Now you're talking in circles.

373
00:35:39.771 --> 00:35:41.830
So. she's on the list..

374
00:35:41.973 --> 00:35:44.635
Wait. shut up.

375
00:35:44.776 --> 00:35:46.744
- At any rate. there was a call.
- Right.

376
00:35:46.878 --> 00:35:51.713
So shouldn't you be able to
trace the call or something?

377
00:35:51.849 --> 00:35:52.816
Trace the call?

378
00:35:52.951 --> 00:35:56.318
That's not something
we do for just anyone.

379
00:35:56.454 --> 00:35:58.319
Are you even aware
of how complicated that is?

380
00:35:58.456 --> 00:36:00.822
'Just anyone' is that what you said?

381
00:36:00.959 --> 00:36:02.517
Stop it! Step back!

382
00:36:02.660 --> 00:36:03.922
What the...

383
00:36:04.062 --> 00:36:07.828
Please. officer.
let's talk like reasonable people.

384
00:36:07.966 --> 00:36:11.527
- They're just kids. don't...
- What are you doing?

385
00:36:11.669 --> 00:36:12.533
No. I mean...

386
00:36:12.670 --> 00:36:17.130
Your daughter never called you
in the first place. okay?

387
00:36:17.275 --> 00:36:21.939
Your son had a dream.
but it was so real that...

388
00:36:23.548 --> 00:36:26.210
You don't believe
anything we said?

389
00:36:28.052 --> 00:36:29.815
Now you're obstructing an officer
in the line of duty...

390
00:36:29.954 --> 00:36:31.114
Step back. Nam-joo.

391
00:36:31.255 --> 00:36:33.519
Officer. should I explain it again?

392
00:36:33.658 --> 00:36:34.420
The way it happened was...

393
00:36:34.559 --> 00:36:38.928
I know. I know.
You yourself saw your daughter die.

394
00:36:39.063 --> 00:36:41.224
But she called you
in the middle of the night?

395
00:36:41.366 --> 00:36:43.527
Does that make any sense?
That's completely ridiculous!

396
00:36:43.668 --> 00:36:46.637
A servant of the people.
talking back like that?

397
00:36:46.771 --> 00:36:48.329
- Then what's your problem?
- Just a moment...

398
00:36:48.473 --> 00:36:49.633
Stop!

399
00:36:54.579 --> 00:36:55.739
This is...

400
00:37:02.954 --> 00:37:09.325
This is my daughter Park Hyun-seo.
My daughter...

401
00:37:09.460 --> 00:37:10.825
I'm the creature.

402
00:37:12.063 --> 00:37:19.128
I ate her... Okay?
And then...

403
00:37:24.575 --> 00:37:28.841
It happened like this.
This is the sewer.

404
00:37:29.380 --> 00:37:31.007
You don't understand?

405
00:37:32.650 --> 00:37:34.709
He's received
psychological treatment?

406
00:37:35.653 --> 00:37:40.613
He's not a bad man. but he's
in shock. We should understand.

407
00:37:40.758 --> 00:37:42.316
- Hey.
- I knew it!

408
00:37:42.460 --> 00:37:46.624
Officer!
My daughter is alive in the sewer!

409
00:37:46.764 --> 00:37:48.425
- Officer?
- Cut it out!

410
00:37:48.566 --> 00:37:50.625
Your putting on
a damn show doesn't help!

411
00:37:50.768 --> 00:37:54.534
My friend's nephew's husband's
brother-in-law is a cop.

412
00:37:54.672 --> 00:37:56.037
maybe we should contact him...?

413
00:37:56.174 --> 00:37:57.937
Right. I'm sure he'd
bend over backwards for us.

414
00:37:58.076 --> 00:38:02.342
You're a college graduate.
can't you even persuade a cop?

415
00:38:02.480 --> 00:38:04.914
What's college got to do with it?

416
00:38:05.550 --> 00:38:07.711
I put you through school
selling cup ramen. and you...

417
00:38:07.852 --> 00:38:09.717
- Dad.
- Huh?

418
00:38:09.854 --> 00:38:12.823
How long's it been since
she's eaten? Down in the sewer?

419
00:38:14.559 --> 00:38:16.322
What's there to eat down there?

420
00:38:30.675 --> 00:38:32.142
You over there!

421
00:38:32.276 --> 00:38:34.039
Hey blondie. stop!

422
00:38:36.280 --> 00:38:37.406
Run!

423
00:38:37.949 --> 00:38:39.109
Out of the way!

424
00:38:40.351 --> 00:38:41.716
Catch them!

425
00:38:43.354 --> 00:38:45.822
Out of the way! Quick!

426
00:38:45.957 --> 00:38:48.824
This way! Hurry up!

427
00:38:48.960 --> 00:38:50.120
Gang-du. hurry up!

428
00:38:50.862 --> 00:38:53.023
- Which floor?
- Close the door! Quick!

429
00:38:54.265 --> 00:38:57.325
I'm coming down. but I'm
in the elevator. so...

430
00:38:57.468 --> 00:38:58.730
Where is he?

431
00:38:58.870 --> 00:39:00.428
B4 A3?

432
00:39:01.172 --> 00:39:02.036
What did I just say?

433
00:39:02.173 --> 00:39:03.731
B4 A3!

434
00:39:05.176 --> 00:39:08.543
A3. Where's A3?

435
00:39:08.679 --> 00:39:10.408
There it is!

436
00:39:11.449 --> 00:39:14.111
Stop! Catch that car.

437
00:39:16.854 --> 00:39:19.414
Hurry! Open the door!

438
00:39:19.557 --> 00:39:22.321
Go! Step on it!

439
00:39:24.462 --> 00:39:25.429
- Nam-joo!
- Hurry up!

440
00:39:25.563 --> 00:39:26.530
Where is Nam-joo?

441
00:39:26.664 --> 00:39:27.631
Where is she?

442
00:39:27.765 --> 00:39:29.232
Did they catch her?

443
00:39:29.367 --> 00:39:30.026
- Oh. shit.
- Where?

444
00:39:30.168 --> 00:39:31.328
Where?

445
00:39:31.469 --> 00:39:33.130
- There. there!
- Where?

446
00:39:33.271 --> 00:39:33.635
Over there.

447
00:39:33.771 --> 00:39:35.432
That idiot!

448
00:39:35.573 --> 00:39:39.634
How could you leave
your only sister?

449
00:39:39.777 --> 00:39:42.143
- We can pick her up!
- Pick her up then!

450
00:39:42.280 --> 00:39:44.908
- She's always been slow...
- Mister. can you stop here?

451
00:39:45.049 --> 00:39:45.515
Hurry up!

452
00:39:45.650 --> 00:39:47.515
What a dimwit!

453
00:39:47.652 --> 00:39:49.210
- Hurry it up. will you?
- Quick! Quick!

454
00:39:49.353 --> 00:39:55.121
Hey. family!
Everyone stop. Stop the van.

455
00:39:57.662 --> 00:39:58.924
Hey. stop!

456
00:40:01.465 --> 00:40:03.126
Just close it! Close!

457
00:40:14.178 --> 00:40:15.543
Did we make it?

458
00:40:19.250 --> 00:40:20.217
That does it.

459
00:40:20.351 --> 00:40:21.716
This won't do.

460
00:40:21.886 --> 00:40:27.552
The basic fee for pickup and the
items you ordered is 7.400 dollars.

461
00:40:27.658 --> 00:40:30.821
Including the Han River sewer map.

462
00:40:30.962 --> 00:40:35.331
Plus. we brushed off
a cop in the parking lot.

463
00:40:35.466 --> 00:40:38.435
and two police cars on the road.

464
00:40:38.569 --> 00:40:45.441
Anyway. including hazard fees.
the total is 11.400 dollars.

465
00:40:46.077 --> 00:40:47.442
One of the escaping family...

466
00:40:47.578 --> 00:40:49.842
Wow. Gang-du on TV!

467
00:40:50.748 --> 00:40:52.613
That's my citizen ID photo.

468
00:40:52.750 --> 00:40:55.310
It's from one of those
subway photo booths?

469
00:40:55.453 --> 00:40:58.911
Hey. we should tape this and
show it to Hyun-seo. Daddy on TV...

470
00:40:59.056 --> 00:41:00.421
Jesus...

471
00:41:02.660 --> 00:41:08.121
We don't accept these. If you're
short on cash. we accept cards.

472
00:41:10.067 --> 00:41:12.331
We'll just take the card.

473
00:41:14.672 --> 00:41:18.438
<i>The blonde one.</i>
<i>who made direct contact with it.</i>

474
00:41:18.576 --> 00:41:21.636
<i>He's the stupidest of all.</i>

475
00:41:21.779 --> 00:41:24.714
That bitch!
Listen to the mouth on her.

476
00:41:24.849 --> 00:41:27.909
<i>He pounced on me</i>
<i>and slammed me to the floor.</i>

477
00:41:28.052 --> 00:41:31.715
<i>I think he gave me arthritis.</i>
<i>I'll need treatment. I'm sure.</i>

478
00:41:31.856 --> 00:41:32.914
<i>That's what he's like.</i>

479
00:41:33.057 --> 00:41:34.319
I know who she is.

480
00:41:34.458 --> 00:41:37.120
Like we can't recognize her
through that voice disguiser?

481
00:41:38.562 --> 00:41:40.826
But they keep reporting on us.

482
00:41:40.965 --> 00:41:43.968
<i>The superior archer who escaped</i>
<i>In addition. the daughter among</i>
<i>the escaped family members</i>

483
00:41:43.968 --> 00:41:46.630
<i>The superior archer who escaped</i>
<i>is confirmed to be Park Nam-joo.</i>
<i>national bronze medalist in archery.</i>

484
00:41:46.771 --> 00:41:49.740
What the hell?
How come there's nothing about me?

485
00:41:49.874 --> 00:41:52.434
There's nothing special about you.

486
00:41:53.077 --> 00:41:55.944
Plenty of unemployed
university grads these days...

487
00:41:56.747 --> 00:41:59.307
I sacrificed my youth for
the democratization of our country.

488
00:41:59.950 --> 00:42:02.418
and those fuckers
won't even give me a job.

489
00:42:03.654 --> 00:42:05.815
The passwords are all 4989?

490
00:42:05.956 --> 00:42:08.516
There's a white truck outside.

491
00:42:09.060 --> 00:42:10.925
It's a disinfection truck.
you can take it.

492
00:42:14.165 --> 00:42:19.125
<i>expressed concern that Korea is</i>
<i>not adequately quarantining.</i>

493
00:42:19.270 --> 00:42:22.831
- <i>the infected. The U.S. also...</i>
- Come on. let's go.

494
00:42:27.178 --> 00:42:29.043
That's the truck?

495
00:42:29.780 --> 00:42:31.304
Does it really work?

496
00:42:31.849 --> 00:42:35.216
This is what you got
after spending all your assets?

497
00:42:36.253 --> 00:42:40.314
This gun is...
Fuck. we're not boy scouts.

498
00:42:41.459 --> 00:42:43.427
And why only two disinfectant suits?

499
00:42:43.561 --> 00:42:46.325
So two of us should just
creep around hiding?

500
00:42:46.464 --> 00:42:49.024
Dad. shouldn't this be yellow?

501
00:42:49.166 --> 00:42:51.225
If it's not yellow.
they're bound to catch us.

502
00:42:51.369 --> 00:42:55.829
Wow. this map is
the topping on the cake.

503
00:42:55.973 --> 00:42:58.533
The red circles indicate sewers?

504
00:42:58.676 --> 00:43:01.645
You spent 500 dollars on this?

505
00:43:01.779 --> 00:43:02.541
Really?

506
00:43:02.680 --> 00:43:06.707
But... I got it from a civil servant
who knows the sewer system.

507
00:43:06.851 --> 00:43:09.615
It's photocopied
on the back of used paper.

508
00:43:09.754 --> 00:43:11.517
Hey. a guard post. Get down!

509
00:43:13.657 --> 00:43:16.217
Cover up. quickly!
Your blonde hair is showing.

510
00:43:16.961 --> 00:43:18.121
Get down quickly!

511
00:43:18.662 --> 00:43:21.825
Whatever. you two handle it.

512
00:43:25.136 --> 00:43:27.036
<i>Biohazard</i>

513
00:43:44.855 --> 00:43:49.224
What? If that's their attitude.
why even bother?

514
00:43:49.360 --> 00:43:51.521
Bunch of lazy bums.

515
00:43:51.662 --> 00:43:53.129
Quiet! Stop.

516
00:44:18.656 --> 00:44:19.816
Mr. Park?

517
00:44:22.259 --> 00:44:23.521
Mr. Bacteria?

518
00:44:26.263 --> 00:44:27.730
Lower your mask.

519
00:44:34.872 --> 00:44:37.432
This definitely
a Daesung disinfectant truck.

520
00:44:38.375 --> 00:44:40.138
But are you Daesung people?

521
00:44:46.150 --> 00:44:51.019
Yes. but we're a different team.

522
00:44:52.056 --> 00:44:53.523
Oh. really?

523
00:44:55.559 --> 00:44:57.424
I'm Manager Cho
from the district office.

524
00:45:00.965 --> 00:45:02.125
Don't you know who I am?

525
00:45:03.167 --> 00:45:08.036
You know that 14 different companies
are doing the fumigation on shifts?

526
00:45:09.573 --> 00:45:12.337
But Daesung just
barged in at the end.

527
00:45:12.476 --> 00:45:15.445
To the other companies.
it seems odd.

528
00:45:16.080 --> 00:45:18.514
So I spoke with
President Kwak yesterday...

529
00:45:23.153 --> 00:45:24.814
Not this! No!

530
00:45:26.557 --> 00:45:27.922
Let go...

531
00:45:33.764 --> 00:45:36.631
Manager Cho. this is all I have
with me right now.

532
00:45:36.767 --> 00:45:40.635
Sorry. I'll see you later.

533
00:45:55.252 --> 00:45:57.914
Hey. Gang-du.

534
00:46:25.849 --> 00:46:28.317
Hyun-seo.
It's your Dad.

535
00:46:29.553 --> 00:46:31.418
Hyun-seo!

536
00:46:43.934 --> 00:46:45.196
Hyun-seo!

537
00:46:59.650 --> 00:47:00.810
Park Hyun-seo!

538
00:47:02.953 --> 00:47:04.420
Hyun-seo!

539
00:47:07.057 --> 00:47:08.524
Hyun-seo!

540
00:47:12.062 --> 00:47:13.723
Hyun-seo!

541
00:47:17.267 --> 00:47:18.928
Hyun-seo!

542
00:47:21.572 --> 00:47:25.030
Why does he have to do that?
He's not a kid.

543
00:47:25.175 --> 00:47:26.733
Let him be.

544
00:47:27.478 --> 00:47:29.946
He wants to disinfect himself.

545
00:47:31.849 --> 00:47:37.310
He's worried he'll
pass the virus on to Hyun-seo.

546
00:47:38.255 --> 00:47:39.722
Virus...

547
00:47:41.558 --> 00:47:45.426
All of us are fine. why do they
keep going on about a fucking virus?

548
00:47:45.562 --> 00:47:50.124
If the government says so.
we have to accept it. What can we do?

549
00:47:50.968 --> 00:47:53.528
Is it the virus
that's making me so sleepy?

550
00:47:54.672 --> 00:47:55.639
Hyun-seo...

551
00:47:55.773 --> 00:47:59.231
Look on the ground for footprints.

552
00:48:00.077 --> 00:48:06.209
Hey. did Hyun-seo describe any
special traits of the sewer?

553
00:48:06.350 --> 00:48:07.817
Special traits?

554
00:48:07.951 --> 00:48:10.010
We need some kind of hint here.

555
00:48:10.154 --> 00:48:15.524
Hyun-seo said it was a big sewer.
Look how big this is.

556
00:48:15.659 --> 00:48:18.628
Yes. it seems we'll find something.

557
00:48:18.762 --> 00:48:23.825
Yeah. sure!
Wandering blindly through the sewers...

558
00:48:23.967 --> 00:48:25.332
We need to think of a better way.

559
00:48:25.469 --> 00:48:29.235
Stop complaining! Put your time into
searching another sewer instead.

560
00:48:29.373 --> 00:48:34.037
Hey tortoise! Just try to keep up.
Slow-ass bronze medalist.

561
00:48:34.178 --> 00:48:35.543
- You wanna die?
- Wait!

562
00:48:39.650 --> 00:48:41.311
Hyun-seo! Hyun-seo!

563
00:48:41.452 --> 00:48:42.714
Turn it off.

564
00:48:46.056 --> 00:48:48.820
Something moved there.

565
00:49:07.177 --> 00:49:08.337
Move!

566
00:49:08.479 --> 00:49:10.003
It's this way!

567
00:49:14.651 --> 00:49:15.913
Get down!

568
00:49:21.058 --> 00:49:22.218
What is this?

569
00:49:25.062 --> 00:49:26.529
It's just water!

570
00:49:27.664 --> 00:49:28.824
God damn it!

571
00:49:30.868 --> 00:49:32.233
How typical of you.

572
00:49:33.270 --> 00:49:34.828
Sorry. Dad.

573
00:49:37.975 --> 00:49:39.636
Did you pee?

574
00:49:39.777 --> 00:49:43.338
Because of the bangs. a little.

575
00:49:46.850 --> 00:49:49.318
Why are they going around shooting?

576
00:49:55.959 --> 00:50:00.623
Wow. this cave really does lead
to the Han River!

577
00:50:00.764 --> 00:50:02.823
It's not a cave. it's a sewer.

578
00:50:04.168 --> 00:50:07.331
They're all connected like this.

579
00:50:31.562 --> 00:50:34.827
Gosh. it's hard to make a living.

580
00:50:34.965 --> 00:50:37.229
Do we really have to go?

581
00:50:38.569 --> 00:50:40.332
So you're not hungry?

582
00:50:40.470 --> 00:50:42.734
No. I'm hungry!

583
00:50:43.674 --> 00:50:48.941
If we do this once.
we'll eat well for a whole month.

584
00:50:49.680 --> 00:50:51.307
- Don't you know that?
- I do.

585
00:51:04.862 --> 00:51:06.830
Wow. there's money too.

586
00:51:07.664 --> 00:51:09.325
Don't touch it.

587
00:51:09.466 --> 00:51:11.627
Why not? I'm taking it.

588
00:51:11.768 --> 00:51:15.226
If we take that too. it's theft.

589
00:51:15.372 --> 00:51:16.930
Put it back now. okay?

590
00:51:18.976 --> 00:51:22.036
We're stealing from this place anyway.

591
00:51:24.748 --> 00:51:29.117
Se-joo. this is not theft.

592
00:51:29.853 --> 00:51:33.914
We're now doing 'seo-ri'.

593
00:51:34.858 --> 00:51:37.418
Like melon seo-ri at a farm.

594
00:51:41.365 --> 00:51:46.325
Hey. do you even know
what seo-ri means?

595
00:51:48.672 --> 00:51:51.539
No? The generation gap
is pretty big.

596
00:51:51.675 --> 00:51:56.135
It's an old borrowing game kids play.
So. seo-ri is a right of the hungry.

597
00:52:11.461 --> 00:52:12.621
Run!

598
00:55:37.067 --> 00:55:39.228
Hey.

599
00:55:45.575 --> 00:55:49.136
What should I do?

600
00:55:52.349 --> 00:55:53.714
Are you okay?

601
00:56:58.248 --> 00:57:02.617
Look at that... Isn't that amazing?
In this situation?

602
00:57:02.752 --> 00:57:04.515
Wake him up. there's no time.

603
00:57:04.654 --> 00:57:08.215
Let him sleep a minute.
He needs to sleep every so often.

604
00:57:08.358 --> 00:57:12.021
Should we leave him here?
He's no help anyway.

605
00:57:12.162 --> 00:57:13.720
Kids. wait a minute.

606
00:57:17.367 --> 00:57:18.527
Sit down.

607
00:57:26.276 --> 00:57:31.908
In your view.
is Gang-du really so pathetic?

608
00:57:33.550 --> 00:57:35.017
- Yup.
- Yes.

609
00:57:37.554 --> 00:57:44.323
You wouldn't know it.
but he was a really smart kid.

610
00:57:44.461 --> 00:57:50.627
For example. when he was two.
he'd sit in front of the village store.

611
00:57:50.767 --> 00:57:54.328
and everyone walking by
would ask him directions.

612
00:57:54.471 --> 00:57:58.237
That's how smart he looked.

613
00:58:05.649 --> 00:58:09.415
As you know.
when he was young.

614
00:58:10.654 --> 00:58:12.315
I was out of my mind.

615
00:58:12.455 --> 00:58:14.923
hardly ever coming home.
staying out all night.

616
00:58:15.759 --> 00:58:20.321
And this poor boy with no mother.

617
00:58:21.865 --> 00:58:24.129
he must have been so hungry.

618
00:58:24.267 --> 00:58:27.634
Going around.
doing seo-ri all the time.

619
00:58:27.771 --> 00:58:31.036
Raising himself on organic farms.

620
00:58:31.174 --> 00:58:35.133
Whenever he got caught.
he'd get beaten up.

621
00:58:36.179 --> 00:58:45.019
In this way. he lacked protein
when he needed it most.

622
00:58:45.155 --> 00:58:51.025
So that's why. every now and then.
he dozes off like a sick rooster.

623
00:58:54.264 --> 00:58:55.731
I think something up there...

624
00:58:58.668 --> 00:59:02.331
...must have gone wrong. too.

625
00:59:14.150 --> 00:59:18.314
Have any of you heard it?

626
00:59:19.856 --> 00:59:24.725
The heartbreak of a parent
who's lost a child...

627
00:59:26.963 --> 00:59:29.932
When a parent's heart breaks.

628
00:59:30.066 --> 00:59:33.433
the sound can travel for miles.

629
00:59:34.170 --> 00:59:38.539
So. I really need to say this to you.

630
00:59:38.675 --> 00:59:43.408
Be as nice to Gang-du as you can.

631
00:59:43.546 --> 00:59:47.312
Don't scold him. okay?

632
00:59:47.450 --> 00:59:52.513
Like last time. "Why'd you
grab another girl's hand. moron?"

633
00:59:52.655 --> 00:59:57.217
You should never say
things like that to him. ok?

634
01:00:01.965 --> 01:00:07.631
You know? I spend most of the day
in the small food stand with him.

635
01:00:07.771 --> 01:00:10.535
So whenever I hear him fart.

636
01:00:10.673 --> 01:00:15.337
I can tell right away
if he's in B- or A+ condition.

637
01:00:16.279 --> 01:00:18.611
What do you two know?

638
01:00:19.749 --> 01:00:24.311
But even still... our Hyun-seo...

639
01:00:24.454 --> 01:00:26.012
Hyun-seo?

640
01:00:26.856 --> 01:00:28.721
Hey. you're...

641
01:00:28.858 --> 01:00:30.018
It's watching.

642
01:00:30.660 --> 01:00:31.820
Huh?

643
01:00:34.464 --> 01:00:35.726
It's watching us.

644
01:01:09.165 --> 01:01:10.325
Fire!

645
01:02:03.953 --> 01:02:05.113
Do you see it?

646
01:02:15.665 --> 01:02:18.133
What's going on?

647
01:02:18.868 --> 01:02:21.336
Hyun... Hyun-seo!

648
01:02:21.471 --> 01:02:24.031
Quiet! It's moving!

649
01:02:27.277 --> 01:02:29.438
- What are you doing? Make sure it's dead!
- Wait!

650
01:02:30.146 --> 01:02:32.410
It... It's running away!

651
01:02:32.949 --> 01:02:34.712
Don't get too close!

652
01:02:37.053 --> 01:02:38.213
Shoot!

653
01:02:38.755 --> 01:02:39.813
Dad!

654
01:02:43.660 --> 01:02:47.027
Shoot it in the legs!

655
01:02:48.965 --> 01:02:50.227
Shoot. right now!

656
01:02:58.174 --> 01:02:59.539
It's over there!

657
01:03:08.051 --> 01:03:09.814
- The bullets...
- No bullets!

658
01:03:13.156 --> 01:03:15.317
- Where did it go?
- Are you trying to kill us?

659
01:03:30.573 --> 01:03:32.040
Let's go to the truck.

660
01:03:34.677 --> 01:03:36.542
You all go on!

661
01:03:36.679 --> 01:03:39.705
I'm gonna finish that thing off!

662
01:03:39.849 --> 01:03:40.816
Just run!

663
01:03:40.950 --> 01:03:42.611
- Anyone got any bullets?
- I've got one left.

664
01:03:42.752 --> 01:03:45.516
Good. Give it to me.
and get to the truck.

665
01:03:45.655 --> 01:03:46.519
Dad! Come on!

666
01:03:46.656 --> 01:03:48.715
- Don't worry about me. go to the truck!
- Dad!

667
01:03:48.858 --> 01:03:50.416
Dad! Just come here!

668
01:03:59.969 --> 01:04:02.028
I'll take you down
with one shot this time.

669
01:04:02.171 --> 01:04:03.229
Get up here!

670
01:04:04.173 --> 01:04:05.538
Huh. what's that?

671
01:04:05.675 --> 01:04:08.143
Nam-joo!
What are you doing?

672
01:04:08.277 --> 01:04:09.835
- Nam-joo!
- When did she go out?

673
01:04:09.979 --> 01:04:11.606
Go back!

674
01:04:13.449 --> 01:04:17.510
Oh. no... Hey!
Somebody come get Nam-joo!

675
01:04:18.054 --> 01:04:20.113
- Stop playing around!
- Let go!

676
01:04:20.256 --> 01:04:22.520
Hurry back! Quick!

677
01:04:45.348 --> 01:04:47.407
No! Dad! No!

678
01:04:48.051 --> 01:04:49.814
Fuck! No!

679
01:04:51.054 --> 01:04:52.214
Dad!

680
01:05:24.454 --> 01:05:25.182
Dad...

681
01:05:26.956 --> 01:05:29.015
Dad. wake up!

682
01:05:29.358 --> 01:05:31.622
Dad. the soldiers are coming.

683
01:05:31.761 --> 01:05:32.728
Dad!

684
01:05:32.862 --> 01:05:34.227
You two. get outta here! Quick!

685
01:05:34.363 --> 01:05:35.921
Fuck!

686
01:05:36.065 --> 01:05:38.431
We should never have...

687
01:05:38.568 --> 01:05:40.035
Dad. what about Hyun-seo?

688
01:05:40.169 --> 01:05:42.933
Hyun-seo... We can't get caught.
Hurry. hurry...

689
01:05:43.072 --> 01:05:43.936
Run! Run!

690
01:05:44.073 --> 01:05:45.131
Dad!

691
01:05:45.274 --> 01:05:51.611
What about Hyun-seo... Dad...

692
01:06:16.072 --> 01:06:17.334
Dad!

693
01:06:22.178 --> 01:06:24.009
Freeze!

694
01:06:25.148 --> 01:06:27.912
Infected family located!
One captured. one dead.

695
01:06:28.050 --> 01:06:29.608
Hey. come here right now!

696
01:06:30.353 --> 01:06:33.322
Yes. sir.
Quickly!

697
01:06:35.691 --> 01:06:38.216
We have tragic news.

698
01:06:38.961 --> 01:06:44.922
Sgt. Donald of the 8th U.S. Army. who
through his act of courage revealed.

699
01:06:45.067 --> 01:06:48.230
to the world the existence of
the virus. died today at 4:20pm.

700
01:06:48.371 --> 01:06:50.737
As condolences flood in
from all over the world.

701
01:06:50.873 --> 01:06:55.537
8th U.S. Army Commander Greenfield
held a rare press conference.

702
01:06:55.678 --> 01:06:57.703
to express his condolences.

703
01:06:57.847 --> 01:07:03.308
Meanwhile the U.S. and WHO. citing
the failure of the Korean government
<i>World Health Organization. Geneva. Switzerland</i>

704
01:07:03.452 --> 01:07:07.115
to secure the remaining two
infected family members.

705
01:07:07.256 --> 01:07:10.623
or to capture the creature in question.

706
01:07:10.760 --> 01:07:13.627
have announced
a policy of direct intervention.
<i>Centers for Disease Control. Atlanta. US</i>

707
01:07:13.763 --> 01:07:17.824
Yes. in this context.
the unprecedented use of...

708
01:07:17.967 --> 01:07:20.527
'Agent Yellow'. is that correct?

709
01:07:20.670 --> 01:07:22.035
Yes. that's correct.

710
01:07:22.171 --> 01:07:25.629
Agent Yellow. which has been
chosen for use here in Korea.

711
01:07:25.775 --> 01:07:29.336
is a state-of-the-art chemical
and deployment system.

712
01:07:29.478 --> 01:07:35.007
recently developed by the U.S. to fight
virus outbreaks or biological terror.
<i>US. chose to input Agent Yellow</i>

713
01:07:35.151 --> 01:07:39.417
This extremely powerful and
effective system. once activated.

714
01:07:39.555 --> 01:07:42.820
completely annihilates
all biological agents.

715
01:07:42.959 --> 01:07:45.519
within a radius of
dozens of kilometers.

716
01:07:49.765 --> 01:07:52.325
<i>'Agent Yellow Is Unsafe'</i>
<i>Citizen groups issue strong protest.</i>

717
01:07:52.468 --> 01:07:55.335
<i>Virus carrier Park showing</i>
<i>symptoms similar to common cold.</i>

718
01:08:13.556 --> 01:08:18.016
<i>Indeed. we are trying to provide</i>
<i>Mr. Park the most pleasant...</i>

719
01:08:18.160 --> 01:08:19.525
<i>environment that a patient could want...</i>

720
01:08:19.662 --> 01:08:22.722
<i>We are doing our best</i>
<i>to accommodate Mr. Park Gang-du...</i>

721
01:08:22.865 --> 01:08:25.425
- <i>I see.</i>
- <i>But he didn't cooperate...</i>

722
01:09:08.477 --> 01:09:11.708
<i>Wanted.; Infected Family</i>

723
01:09:24.760 --> 01:09:31.029
<i>Deceased / Captured</i>

724
01:09:52.455 --> 01:09:55.913
- When did you get here?
- Just a minute ago.

725
01:09:57.159 --> 01:09:58.922
Nobody followed you. right?

726
01:09:59.061 --> 01:10:01.325
It's okay. I checked carefully.

727
01:10:01.464 --> 01:10:04.627
And Nam-joo? Where's Nam-joo?

728
01:10:04.767 --> 01:10:05.825
Nam-joo? Why?

729
01:10:05.968 --> 01:10:07.936
You travel separately. you two?

730
01:10:28.357 --> 01:10:32.726
So if you just type into the office's
computer. it shows up?

731
01:10:32.862 --> 01:10:33.829
Really?

732
01:10:33.963 --> 01:10:36.431
Hyun-seo called late at night. right?

733
01:10:36.565 --> 01:10:39.033
Then the transmitter will
be listed in the call records.

734
01:10:39.168 --> 01:10:43.229
That means she's within
200 meters of a transmitter.

735
01:10:44.073 --> 01:10:45.438
That's simple.

736
01:10:47.076 --> 01:10:49.044
It's that easy to get her location?

737
01:10:49.178 --> 01:10:52.306
That's right. you should have
come to me earlier.

738
01:10:52.448 --> 01:10:55.611
Is all of your family
so dumb all the time?

739
01:10:55.751 --> 01:11:00.211
Right... all those sewers... fuck.

740
01:11:00.356 --> 01:11:03.223
It's okay. finding her
is just a matter of time.

741
01:11:03.359 --> 01:11:06.021
All thanks to you.

742
01:11:07.363 --> 01:11:12.323
You were always busy protesting.
when did you ever study?

743
01:11:12.468 --> 01:11:15.335
It must be really hard
getting work at a telecom firm.

744
01:11:16.172 --> 01:11:18.231
Still. I'm just a salaryman.

745
01:11:19.275 --> 01:11:22.438
But you must make 60-70 grand a year?

746
01:11:23.746 --> 01:11:25.714
My credit card debt is 60-70 grand.

747
01:11:25.848 --> 01:11:28.908
- Look.
- Wait...

748
01:11:29.051 --> 01:11:32.214
The time. the number...

749
01:11:32.354 --> 01:11:33.912
Here. This is it!

